author: Nerdstalgic
description:
The Fresh Prince of Bel-Air is a 90s sitcom legend, launching Will Smith’s acting career and redefining the genre with its perfect blend of humor, heart, and cultural impact. But did you know that a young Kevin Hart once starred in a short-lived, Fresh Prince-style sitcom that completely flopped?    

The Big House was a 2004 sitcom that tried to flip the Fresh Prince formula upside down, but despite Hart’s star power, the show was cancelled before its first season even finished airing.

#kevinhart #willsmith #freshprinceofbelair #sitcom
title: Why Kevin Hart's WEIRD Fresh Prince Ripoff Failed Miserably
